<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16385&amp;p=202828#p202828"><![CDATA[
Personally, I would set a constant tone, wait a few frames, turn the volume off (LDA #0, STA $4000), wait a few frames, turn the volume on again, wait a few frames, and turn the volume back off.<br /><br />It could also be done with careful settings of the 'loop' and 'length counter', but it may not sound exactly like what you want, and is very tricky.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7008">dougeff</a> — Sat Aug 19, 2017 6:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
